    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                        <date>Sep 7</date>
                        <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>I am much obliged for your very kind note.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I should have been pleased to have given permission for the translation, but my work on Orchids was translated by the late Professor Bronn &amp; published in Stuttgard by E. Schweizerbart.<ref target="#foot.f3"/> My Monograph on the Cirripedia was originally published by the Ray Society, but can now be purchased at Hardwick’s 192 Piccadilly. It consists of 2 large Vols. with numerous plates &amp; I believe but I am not sure that the price is £1–1–<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
                        <p>Pray believe me | Dear Sir yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p>
                    </div>
                </div>   
               
                
                
            </div>
            
            
            <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-4609.xml">letter from Hermann Kindt, 5 September 1864</ref> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 12).</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f2">Kindt had asked whether it was permitted to publish translated extracts from <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_6010.xml"><hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi></ref> (<hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 12, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-4609.xml">letter from Hermann Kindt, 5 September 1864</ref>).</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f3"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_657.xml">Heinrich Georg Bronn</ref>’s translation of <hi rend="italic">Orchids</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_951.xml">Bronn trans. 1862</ref>) was published by <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4246.xml">E. Schweizerbart</ref> in Stuttgart.</note>
                <note xml:id="foot.f4"><ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4837.xml"><hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi> (1851)</ref>, <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4838.xml"><hi rend="italic">Living Cirripedia</hi> (1854)</ref>. <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2113.xml">Robert Hardwicke</ref> was publisher to the Ray Society. The total cost of the two volumes was £2 2<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2661.xml">Freeman 1977</ref>).</note>
            </div>
        
